    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped white pak choi base</strong> to the pan with the<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>black bean paste</strong>, 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> cold water and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 2 min further</p><p>After 2 min add the <strong>green pak choi tops</strong> and cook for a final minute – this is your <strong>pak choi & baby corn black bean stir-fry</strong></p>",
